{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The library is now 100% Swift 6 compatible, and has been done in a way that is full backwards"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compatible. If your project does not have strict concurrency warnings turned on, then updating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Composable Architecture to 1.15.0 should not cause any compilation errors. However, if you have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strict concurrency turned on, then you may come across a few situations you need to update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Enum cases as function references","anchor":"Enum-cases-as-function-references","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is common to use the case of enum as a function, such as mapping on an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect"},{"text":" to bundle","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"its output into an action:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["return client.fetch()","  .map(Action.response)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In strict concurrency mode this may fail with a message like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"🛑 Converting non-sendable function value to ‘@Sendable (Value) -> Action’ may introduce data races","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two ways to fix this. You can either open the closure explicitly instead of using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Action.response"},{"type":"text","text":" as a function:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["return client.fetch()","  .map { .response($0) }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is also an upcoming Swift feature that will fix this. You can enable it in an SPM package"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by adding a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enableUpcomingFeature"},{"type":"text","text":" to its Swift settings:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["swiftSettings: [","  .enableUpcomingFeature(\"InferSendableFromCaptures\"),","]),"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And you can "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/blog\/using-upcoming-feature-flags\/","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by navigating to your project’s build settings in Xcode, and adding a new “Other Swift Flags” flag:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["-enable-upcoming-feature InferSendableFromCaptures"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Mig